WEBVTT

00:03.333 --> 00:05.875
[ Celeste's "Little Runaway" plays ]

00:05.959 --> 00:07.417
Meredith: <i>This job isn't easy.</i>

00:08.792 --> 00:11.041
<i>The sheer amount of pressure and loss</i>

00:11.166 --> 00:13.917
<i>that we square off against every day...</i>

00:14.000 --> 00:16.125
<i>♪ I don't see nothin' comin' ♪</i>

00:16.208 --> 00:17.417
<i>...can leave you exhausted...</i>

00:17.500 --> 00:19.083
<i>♪ Maybe they were all misplaced ♪</i>

00:19.166 --> 00:20.583
<i>...or helpless.</i>

00:20.667 --> 00:22.917
You're okay. You're okay.

00:23.000 --> 00:26.000
<i>♪ Good news, I could use some ♪</i>

00:26.083 --> 00:28.959
Meredith: <i>You're going to need to find</i>
<i>an outlet for the stress.</i>

00:29.458 --> 00:32.417
<i>♪ One man revolution ♪</i>

00:32.500 --> 00:34.041
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

00:35.875 --> 00:39.291
<i>♪ Hallelujah, take me to ya ♪</i>

00:39.375 --> 00:42.125
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm lost alone again ♪</i>

00:42.542 --> 00:43.625
<i>♪ Hallelujah, take me to ya ♪</i>

00:43.709 --> 00:44.583
<i>Maybe it's physical...</i>

00:45.917 --> 00:48.333
<i>♪ I don't believe, but I'll pretend ♪</i>

00:48.417 --> 00:50.583
<i>...maybe it's emotional...</i>

00:50.667 --> 00:52.458
<i>♪ Your little runaway</i>
<i>is runnin' out of faith ♪</i>

00:52.542 --> 00:53.917
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:54.000 --> 00:55.917
Hey, buddy. Hey!

00:56.125 --> 00:57.750
Hi. Oh, you're so big.

00:57.875 --> 01:01.166
Mommy misses you both so much.

01:01.500 --> 01:02.917
<i>I love you, Mommy.</i>

01:03.041 --> 01:04.709
I love you. I miss you.

01:05.208 --> 01:06.667
Meredith: <i>...maybe it's family...</i>

01:06.750 --> 01:08.834
<i>♪ Runnin' out of faith, so if you can ♪</i>

01:08.917 --> 01:12.041
<i>...but trust me, you're not</i>
<i>going to survive residency</i>

01:12.166 --> 01:14.000
<i>unless you have a happy place...</i>

01:14.083 --> 01:17.166
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm waitin' ♪</i>

01:17.250 --> 01:19.250
<i>♪ Hallelujah, take me to ya ♪</i>

01:19.333 --> 01:22.125
<i>...somewhere that you</i>
<i>can just escape it all.</i>

01:22.208 --> 01:24.750
<i>♪ 'Cause I'll be waitin' ♪</i>

01:30.834 --> 01:32.291
[ Siren wails ]

01:32.375 --> 01:33.667
Ben: I need another ABD.

01:33.750 --> 01:35.250
Why aren't we there yet?

01:35.333 --> 01:36.750
We're going as fast as we can
without crashing.

01:36.834 --> 01:38.291
Ben: Uh...

01:38.375 --> 01:39.875
You need to tell them
it's him so they're ready.

01:39.959 --> 01:41.917
Okay, Carina, I know you are
scared, but this isn't helping.

01:43.625 --> 01:44.500
"B."

01:44.750 --> 01:46.291
"B"? "B" what, buddy?

01:46.375 --> 01:48.875
"B" positive. That's my blood type.

01:48.959 --> 01:50.291
We'll call ahead and make sure they know.

01:50.375 --> 01:51.542
Give me a 4x4.

01:51.625 --> 01:53.959
Andrea, you are gonna be okay,
Andrea, okay?

01:54.041 --> 01:55.333
[ Groaning ]

01:55.417 --> 01:56.875
Okay?

01:59.834 --> 02:01.041
Reza: Val Ashton.

02:01.125 --> 02:02.917
Two days post extended liver resection.

02:03.000 --> 02:04.542
LFTs are still elevated.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.917
Blood cultures are growing
gram-negative bacteria.

02:07.000 --> 02:10.041
How are you feeling?
Any tenderness or nausea?

02:10.125 --> 02:12.125
Honestly, I think I can get out of bed

02:12.208 --> 02:13.375
and do a couple laps.

02:15.166 --> 02:16.834
She's still septic.

02:16.917 --> 02:18.959
Start her on Levophed, add an antifungal,

02:19.041 --> 02:21.458
and order a repeat CT.

02:21.750 --> 02:24.250
You feel like crap, and you're
acting like you don't.

02:24.333 --> 02:25.417
Why would I --

02:25.500 --> 02:27.166
So I'll let you out of bed
so you can see Luna.

02:27.542 --> 02:29.083
I've tried this your way.

02:29.166 --> 02:30.333
It isn't working.

02:31.500 --> 02:32.583
Val, I know that this --

02:32.667 --> 02:35.000
Please don't say you know how this feels,

02:35.083 --> 02:37.792
because I like you,
and I want to keep liking you.

02:37.875 --> 02:40.041
But unless you've had
a baby that you haven't

02:40.125 --> 02:43.875
been allowed to hold or even see
in person her whole life,

02:43.959 --> 02:45.959
you don't know.

02:47.583 --> 02:49.041
[ Sighs ]

02:50.834 --> 02:53.291
I finally got ahold of Luna's father.

02:53.375 --> 02:55.667
He signed over his parental rights.

02:55.750 --> 02:56.709
Isn't that what you wanted?

02:56.792 --> 02:57.875
Yeah.

02:58.208 --> 03:00.375
But I expected at least a little fight.

03:00.625 --> 03:03.166
Not a text back that says, "Good luck."

03:03.250 --> 03:04.583
Baby emoji.

03:05.458 --> 03:09.250
So, yes, I feel like crap.

03:10.375 --> 03:13.667
I feel sick down to my bones
that I made a child

03:13.750 --> 03:17.208
with someone who doesn't
even care she exists.

03:20.709 --> 03:22.333
Let's get the sepsis under control,

03:22.417 --> 03:24.417
and then we can talk about seeing Luna.

03:24.834 --> 03:26.667
[ Monitor beeping ]

03:32.041 --> 03:34.250
[ Sighs ]

03:34.333 --> 03:37.583
They were out of oat milk,
so it's gonna be almond.

03:38.458 --> 03:39.709
Savages.

03:39.792 --> 03:41.041
Right?

03:43.083 --> 03:44.291
[ Groans ]

03:51.458 --> 03:52.875
Hmm.

03:56.125 --> 03:57.417
You should eat.

03:58.083 --> 03:59.083
Coffee first.

04:00.667 --> 04:02.667
And I don't need a speech about breakfast

04:02.750 --> 04:05.750
and nutrients for my brain
because my brain

04:05.834 --> 04:07.417
is finally turned off.

04:07.500 --> 04:10.417
I'd like to keep it that way
for as long as possible.

04:11.750 --> 04:13.166
Want to get some fresh air?

04:13.375 --> 04:14.667
We could go for a walk.

04:15.875 --> 04:17.291
I'm right where I want to be.

04:25.625 --> 04:28.542
[ Music playing ]

04:36.709 --> 04:38.792
Maggie, I don't know if you are asleep

04:38.875 --> 04:43.000
or if you are ignoring me
or the world entirely, but call.

04:43.083 --> 04:44.375
Link: Still nothing?

04:44.500 --> 04:46.709
Uh, she could be passed out
on the floor from COVID,

04:46.792 --> 04:48.083
and no one would know.

04:48.166 --> 04:50.375
Or -- Or she could be
hit by a car on the I-94

04:50.458 --> 04:51.667
on the way to Wyoming.

04:51.750 --> 04:52.917
What's in Wyoming? I don't know.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.875
But one sister's on a vent
and the other one is missing,

04:55.959 --> 04:57.500
and the last time a sibling was missing,

04:57.583 --> 04:58.959
he was dying on the side of the road, so--

04:59.041 --> 05:00.709
Is my mommy gonna die?

05:00.792 --> 05:03.041
Uh...

05:03.125 --> 05:04.792
It's okay. You can tell me.

05:05.875 --> 05:07.166
[ Sighs ]

05:09.542 --> 05:11.583
Come on, Zo. Let's go inside.

05:14.709 --> 05:16.375
[ Sighs ]

05:16.458 --> 05:17.709
[ Door closes ]

05:17.792 --> 05:19.166
[ Siren wailing in distance]

05:19.250 --> 05:20.500
I called up to the blood bank

05:20.583 --> 05:22.583
to have type "B" blood on standby.

05:22.667 --> 05:24.083
Hopefully, it's a sign.

05:26.166 --> 05:27.959
You know, "be positive"?

05:28.041 --> 05:29.250
Rig's here.

05:32.542 --> 05:33.792
Carina, what the hell?

05:33.875 --> 05:35.166
-It's Andrea.
-What?

05:35.250 --> 05:36.959
Ben: Stab wound to the abdomen,
possibly into the chest.

05:37.041 --> 05:38.417
Slightly hypotensive and tachycardic

05:38.500 --> 05:40.417
after one liter of NS. What happened?

05:40.500 --> 05:41.458
He was following a sex trafficker,

05:41.542 --> 05:42.834
and she attacked him.

05:42.917 --> 05:44.834
They got her. I-I think I'm okay.

05:44.917 --> 05:46.917
Owen: DeLuca, try not to talk.
It's Dr. Hunt.

05:47.000 --> 05:48.625
You're at Grey-Sloan.
Let's get him to trauma one.

05:48.709 --> 05:49.917
Let's move. Schmitt, let's go.

05:50.000 --> 05:51.625
-Carina: Owen.
-Yeah?

05:51.709 --> 05:53.792
Please save him. Please.

05:53.875 --> 05:54.834
Okay.

06:02.500 --> 06:03.375
[ Groans ]

06:03.458 --> 06:04.667
Owen: There's fluid in his abdomen
and around his heart.

06:04.750 --> 06:07.250
-Ben: How you feeling, DeLuca?
-Like I got stabbed.

06:07.583 --> 06:08.750
Chest films are up.

06:09.208 --> 06:10.542
-[ Groans ]
-Okay, let me see.

06:10.625 --> 06:12.125
[ Monitor beeps ]

06:12.375 --> 06:14.500
DeLuca, you have a hemothorax.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.208
I'm gonna have to place
a chest tube, okay?

06:16.291 --> 06:18.500
-Great.
-Schmitt, hang another unit.

06:18.583 --> 06:20.458
[ Groaning ]

06:23.041 --> 06:25.417
[ Grunting ]

06:27.458 --> 06:28.875
Here it comes. Ready?

06:28.959 --> 06:32.000
[ Gasping, groaning ]

06:36.375 --> 06:38.208
Ben: BP's still dropping.

06:39.208 --> 06:40.792
Okay, let's call the OR.
Tell them we're on our way up, okay?

06:40.875 --> 06:41.834
Hey, I want to go with him.

06:41.917 --> 06:43.166
DeLuca: Carina, no.

06:43.250 --> 06:44.583
Andrea, I want to come with you.

06:44.667 --> 06:46.709
Carina, he's right. Please.

06:48.000 --> 06:49.500
Okay, ready? We good?

06:49.583 --> 06:50.917
Oh, God.

06:51.375 --> 06:53.208
Okay, good. Let's go. Move.

06:53.875 --> 06:55.333
[ Groaning ]

07:01.208 --> 07:03.166
[ Sobs ]

07:12.750 --> 07:14.250
Uh, Dr. Webber?

07:15.667 --> 07:17.250
Um...

07:17.917 --> 07:19.250
There's a...

07:19.333 --> 07:21.875
a huge trauma that just
came in, and, um...

07:21.959 --> 07:25.125
-Well, did Hunt ask for help?
-No. Uh...

07:26.417 --> 07:28.875
Did he ask you to come to stare at me?

07:31.208 --> 07:32.667
It's, uh --

07:32.750 --> 07:34.166
It's DeLuca.

07:34.250 --> 07:37.500
He's been stabbed, and, um, I saw him,

07:37.583 --> 07:39.208
and I-I wish I hadn't,

07:39.291 --> 07:41.834
but, um, I did,
and I thought you should know.

07:48.875 --> 07:51.333
[ Seagulls crying ]

08:03.333 --> 08:04.291
Hey!

08:04.375 --> 08:05.792
Hey yourself.

08:06.709 --> 08:08.333
[ Sighs ]

08:11.250 --> 08:12.333
Impressive.

08:12.417 --> 08:13.667
Your turn.

08:13.750 --> 08:15.041
Let's see what you got.

08:15.542 --> 08:17.250
-Okay.
-[ Chuckles ]

08:17.583 --> 08:18.750
There you go.

08:18.834 --> 08:19.959
Just gotta put a little bit
more muscle into it.

08:20.041 --> 08:21.875
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

08:21.959 --> 08:23.291
You know, this is
the first time in my life

08:23.375 --> 08:25.750
I can ever remember
not feeling competitive.

08:26.458 --> 08:27.792
Is this your life?

08:28.375 --> 08:29.542
What?

08:30.625 --> 08:32.458
Well, you said
the first time in your life,

08:32.542 --> 08:34.625
but I don't know.

08:34.792 --> 08:36.125
I'm not so sure.

08:36.709 --> 08:37.667
Are we alive?

08:37.750 --> 08:39.166
I think so.

08:41.875 --> 08:43.709
[ Inhales deeply ]

08:44.875 --> 08:46.458
You look good.

08:46.542 --> 08:48.166
The beach suits you.

08:49.125 --> 08:50.417
You too.

08:54.542 --> 08:57.166
[ Sighs ] I made Zola a grilled cheese.

08:57.250 --> 08:58.667
She's watching a movie with the other two.

08:58.750 --> 09:00.166
[ Sighs ]

09:00.250 --> 09:01.917
Did you actually say anything?

09:02.000 --> 09:04.333
[ Sighs ] Ellis interrupted us
before we got too far.

09:04.417 --> 09:05.709
Which feels like divine intervention

09:05.792 --> 09:08.000
because I have no idea what I would say.

09:08.083 --> 09:11.291
I mean, I can't lie because...lying.

09:11.375 --> 09:14.250
And Zola's so smart she'd just
see right through it.

09:14.333 --> 09:16.500
So you're just gonna keep
making grilled cheeses?

09:17.750 --> 09:19.166
Are you just gonna walk for two hours

09:19.250 --> 09:20.792
every time Scout needs to sleep?

09:20.875 --> 09:22.709
You want to see what happens when I stop?

09:22.792 --> 09:24.250
I'm sorry. I need Maggie.

09:24.333 --> 09:25.792
Maggie is thoughtful and levelheaded,

09:25.875 --> 09:28.166
and I know I have to tell Zola the truth,

09:28.250 --> 09:30.500
but I need help knowing how
to tell her the truth.

09:30.583 --> 09:32.542
She's not picking up.
I have to go get her.

09:32.625 --> 09:34.458
W-What? No, you haven't slept.

09:34.542 --> 09:36.667
You can't stand still. You're not driving.

09:36.750 --> 09:37.834
You haven't slept either.

09:37.917 --> 09:39.792
Okay, deep breaths.

09:39.875 --> 09:41.458
[ Inhales deeply ]

09:41.542 --> 09:43.208
We'll figure this out.

09:43.291 --> 09:47.333
Um, I-I'll just call somebody
that can find Maggie.

09:47.417 --> 09:48.667
Who?

09:48.750 --> 09:50.834
I don't know.

09:50.917 --> 09:52.667
[ Sighs ]

09:52.750 --> 09:54.458
[ Scout crying ]

09:54.542 --> 09:56.458
Ooh.

09:56.542 --> 10:00.333
[ Intercom chatter ]

10:00.417 --> 10:02.125
Hey, where's Carina?

10:02.208 --> 10:03.583
Uh, they headed up to the chapel.

10:03.667 --> 10:05.709
Okay, can you tell her
that DeLuca is stable

10:05.792 --> 10:06.917
and he's on his way to the OR?

10:07.000 --> 10:08.208
Yeah. Thanks.

10:08.291 --> 10:09.375
Who's that?

10:09.750 --> 10:11.291
Uh, it's the woman DeLuca was following.

10:11.375 --> 10:12.542
Detectives need her photo.

10:12.625 --> 10:14.500
Why? You -- You know her?

10:15.667 --> 10:17.542
She was here last night,
and I treated her.

10:17.625 --> 10:18.792
For what?

10:18.875 --> 10:20.917
She said she was mugged. Oh, my God.

10:21.000 --> 10:22.583
-Schmitt, hey, hey.
-Oh, my God. Is this my fault?

10:22.667 --> 10:24.792
No, none of this is your fault.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:35.083 --> 10:36.333
Hi.

10:37.000 --> 10:38.083
What, no gifts?

10:38.792 --> 10:40.000
At the very least, some crosswords,

10:40.083 --> 10:42.917
peanut butter cookies, contraband porn?

10:44.583 --> 10:46.125
Kidding.

10:46.208 --> 10:49.000
I'd trade all that for good conversation.

10:50.208 --> 10:51.625
Okay, if this is about the nurses,

10:51.709 --> 10:53.000
they need to calm down.

10:53.083 --> 10:55.542
We both have COVID. It was no biggie.

10:55.625 --> 10:56.625
What are you talking about?

10:56.709 --> 10:57.834
I went to see Grey.

10:57.917 --> 11:00.000
I needed to see some living scenery.

11:00.208 --> 11:02.041
You would have loved it --
the two of us under blankets,

11:02.125 --> 11:03.500
it was like "On COVID Pond."

11:03.583 --> 11:04.625
It's not funny.

11:04.709 --> 11:05.750
It's a little funny.

11:05.834 --> 11:08.041
We intubated Meredith, Tom.

11:09.542 --> 11:11.041
[ Scoffs ]

11:11.125 --> 11:12.583
You know, if you ever
find yourself thinking about

11:12.667 --> 11:14.667
cheering up kids
in the cancer ward, don't.

11:14.750 --> 11:18.041
Sorry. I'm sorry. I-I just... [ Sighs ]

11:18.125 --> 11:19.667
I just needed to be in a room with someone

11:19.750 --> 11:21.250
who doesn't hate me.

11:22.959 --> 11:24.458
[ Scoffs ]

11:25.375 --> 11:28.709
Well, no one can
clear a remarkably low bar

11:28.792 --> 11:30.333
like Tom Koracick.

11:32.583 --> 11:34.000
Have a seat.

11:40.125 --> 11:41.458
[ Sighs ]

11:45.125 --> 11:47.291
I don't hate you, Altman.

11:48.291 --> 11:49.667
But it would help me to hear you admit

11:49.750 --> 11:52.166
that you never loved me.

11:53.792 --> 11:55.750
You don't have to say it now, but...

11:55.834 --> 11:57.792
You're tired. We're both sc-scared.

11:57.875 --> 12:02.041
But it would help me
to hear it sometime soon.

12:06.917 --> 12:08.166
-Dr. Wilson.
-Yeah?

12:08.250 --> 12:10.333
I've maxed out Ms. Ashton on pressors,

12:10.417 --> 12:12.041
but her MAPS keep dropping.

12:13.792 --> 12:16.083
Her repeat CT shows no fluid,
which means that

12:16.166 --> 12:17.917
what's left of her liver is failing.

12:18.000 --> 12:21.041
Um, start her on liver dialysis

12:21.125 --> 12:23.375
and keep me posted if she gets any worse.

12:27.750 --> 12:29.500
Luna Ashton's mom is your patient, right?

12:29.583 --> 12:30.875
Why?

12:30.959 --> 12:32.083
Luna has a bronchogenic cyst.

12:32.166 --> 12:33.458
I'd like to get her into the OR

12:33.542 --> 12:35.583
before it causes respiratory distress.

12:35.667 --> 12:37.667
Thought you might like to
join me to tell her mom.

12:37.750 --> 12:38.625
No.

12:38.709 --> 12:39.792
Okay, suit yourself.

12:39.875 --> 12:41.375
No, I just -- I don't want you
to tell her either.

12:41.458 --> 12:42.917
I don't want anyone to tell her.

12:43.000 --> 12:45.208
I suppose we could sneak Luna in

12:45.291 --> 12:47.375
and say it was emergent,
that Val was sleeping.

12:47.458 --> 12:48.583
We didn't have time to ask her.

12:48.667 --> 12:50.792
-Really?
-No. What's wrong with you?

12:50.875 --> 12:52.333
She just -- She needs some really

12:52.417 --> 12:54.458
not-terrible news right now.

12:54.542 --> 12:55.834
We all do.

12:55.917 --> 12:57.041
[ Sighs ]

12:58.834 --> 13:01.458
You're gonna do an ex-lap
<i>and </i>a sternotomy?

13:01.542 --> 13:02.792
Is that necessary?

13:02.875 --> 13:04.667
His FAST exam indicates cardiac injury.

13:04.750 --> 13:06.000
Well, then I'll scrub in.

13:06.083 --> 13:07.709
Respectfully, Richard,
you haven't operated in months.

13:07.792 --> 13:09.583
I'm not sure that this is
the way to jump back in.

13:09.667 --> 13:11.333
Well, respectfully, you need the help,

13:11.417 --> 13:13.166
and I'm not about to wake up Bailey

13:13.250 --> 13:15.125
when she's sleeping for the first time
since her mother died.

13:15.208 --> 13:16.750
I'm not asking you to. Get Altman.

13:16.834 --> 13:19.041
Altman's coming off
a 20-hour shift which ended

13:19.125 --> 13:20.667
in putting Meredith Grey on a vent.

13:20.750 --> 13:22.417
She's in no condition to operate.

13:22.500 --> 13:24.625
Look, DeLuca saved my life.

13:25.583 --> 13:27.458
It's only right that I do the same.

13:28.083 --> 13:31.291
When Teddy and I were in Iraq,
this was our job.

13:31.375 --> 13:33.959
To sew up our own people
when they were broken.

13:34.041 --> 13:35.709
We knew the names of
their kids, their dogs,

13:35.792 --> 13:37.834
what compelled them
to serve their country.

13:37.917 --> 13:40.291
Day after day, they'd go
out there, they'd take shrapnel,

13:40.375 --> 13:42.125
and we would take it out,
we'd sew them back up,

13:42.208 --> 13:44.083
and then we'd send them out
there and do it all over again.

13:44.166 --> 13:46.125
There was no sleep, no rest,

13:46.208 --> 13:48.500
no time to let the gravity
of it all sink in.

13:48.583 --> 13:51.000
That was the job, Richard.
Not many people can do it.

13:51.083 --> 13:53.709
Altman can. So, please, get me Altman.

14:00.166 --> 14:02.709
Hey, I got your page,
but DeLuca doesn't need ortho.

14:02.792 --> 14:04.458
<i>I </i>needed ortho.

14:04.542 --> 14:06.709
I saw the woman who did this to DeLuca.

14:06.792 --> 14:07.917
She was here last night.

14:08.000 --> 14:09.750
She said that she was mugged,
but I think that she was lying.

14:09.834 --> 14:12.083
I mean, I-I <i>know </i>she was lying.

14:12.166 --> 14:14.667
And she was asking about the kidnappers,

14:14.750 --> 14:16.542
but I didn't put the pieces together.

14:16.625 --> 14:18.417
And I don't know if I could have,

14:18.500 --> 14:21.208
but I still feel like I <i>should </i>have.

14:21.291 --> 14:23.583
Which is crazy, right?

14:23.667 --> 14:25.667
I-I-I just need to focus
on DeLuca's surgery.

14:25.750 --> 14:27.625
No, you can't scrub in.

14:28.417 --> 14:30.000
This was a pep-talk page.

14:30.375 --> 14:33.041
Okay, then, switch services.
You can do it. Come on.

14:33.709 --> 14:35.166
I want to help.

14:35.375 --> 14:37.917
Then make sure DeLuca gets
a surgeon that's not a wreck.

14:38.291 --> 14:40.667
Said with love, in case you
couldn't tell behind the mask.

14:41.625 --> 14:42.709
[ Sighs ]

14:44.417 --> 14:46.750
It's a small piece of abnormal lung growth

14:46.834 --> 14:49.083
that I need to remove
so she can breathe normally.

14:49.166 --> 14:51.125
And then it'll be my turn
for another surgery.

14:51.208 --> 14:52.291
And then hers.

14:52.375 --> 14:54.083
And then maybe I'll go twice
so you keep me guessing.

14:54.166 --> 14:56.458
Jo: I know it sounds scary,
but Dr. Hayes has done

14:56.542 --> 14:59.166
this surgery countless times.

15:00.667 --> 15:03.667
Has anyone even held her
since she was born?

15:03.750 --> 15:05.792
Well, she has to stay in the incubator

15:05.875 --> 15:07.500
for her own safety, I'm afraid.

15:07.583 --> 15:08.750
That's not right.

15:08.834 --> 15:11.000
She is helpless, and she is scared.

15:11.458 --> 15:14.417
Babies aren't supposed to live
in a plastic container.

15:14.709 --> 15:15.875
[ Val crying ]

15:16.583 --> 15:19.000
You're right, Val. You're right.

15:19.083 --> 15:21.083
You need to see her.
It's not right that you haven't.

15:21.208 --> 15:22.125
Wilson.

15:22.208 --> 15:24.208
I'll bring her to you before
she goes into surgery.

15:24.291 --> 15:25.750
Thank you.

15:25.834 --> 15:27.667
[ Voice breaking ] Thank you so much.

15:27.750 --> 15:29.542
Wilson.

15:31.208 --> 15:32.291
[ Sobbing ]

15:33.750 --> 15:34.834
Teddy: Webber paged.

15:34.917 --> 15:36.834
Yeah, for me. DeLuca got stabbed.

15:36.917 --> 15:39.250
He has a massive hemothorax
and blood in the pericardium.

15:39.333 --> 15:41.000
-Teddy: Sternotomy tray?
-Owen: And Balfour.

15:41.083 --> 15:42.625
We treated a kid in Jordan
who had shrapnel

15:42.709 --> 15:43.875
in the same area.

15:43.959 --> 15:45.625
Right. Texas Hold 'Em guy.

15:45.709 --> 15:47.166
And we sent him home in one piece.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.417
Alright, let's do it again.

15:49.500 --> 15:50.542
Yep.

15:52.083 --> 15:53.792
[ Josh Ronen's "Wake Me Up" plays ]

15:53.875 --> 15:55.000
Ready?

15:55.083 --> 15:57.083
Okay, Schmitt, let's call the blood bank,

15:57.166 --> 15:58.667
make sure there's more coming,
and you can scrub in.

15:58.750 --> 15:59.875
Khan, not Schmitt.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.625
Dr. Schmitt said he needed
to switch services.

16:01.709 --> 16:04.125
I assume because of my time in
Pakistan as a vascular surgeon.

16:04.250 --> 16:05.458
Excellent call, Schmitt.

16:05.542 --> 16:07.583
Alright, you'll assist me
with the sternotomy

16:07.667 --> 16:09.625
while Dr. Hunt explores the abdomen.

16:09.709 --> 16:10.667
We're gonna go fast.

16:10.750 --> 16:11.834
Understood.

16:11.959 --> 16:14.041
Okay, then.

16:14.125 --> 16:15.041
Scalpel.

16:15.583 --> 16:20.500
<i>♪ I hear the thunder calling me ♪</i>

16:24.000 --> 16:26.834
<i>♪ I see the skies ♪</i>

16:26.917 --> 16:29.166
<i>♪ They gently weep ♪</i>

16:29.875 --> 16:31.959
Warren got called to
a four-alarm downtown.

16:32.542 --> 16:34.041
Do you have to go?

16:34.959 --> 16:37.375
Carina, I'm not going anywhere.

16:38.875 --> 16:40.291
Hey, hey.

16:41.458 --> 16:44.542
<i>♪ I hope when I close my eyes ♪</i>

16:45.542 --> 16:48.625
<i>♪ That beauty will find me ♪</i>

16:48.709 --> 16:52.917
Before she died, Mama called us
two halves of one whole.

16:53.625 --> 16:54.834
<i>♪ Will there be someone... ♪</i>

16:54.917 --> 16:57.250
It loses something in translation.

16:57.834 --> 17:01.542
My dad, he thought
we were completely different,

17:01.625 --> 17:07.125
but my mom knew that we couldn't
breathe without the other.

17:07.917 --> 17:11.875
One year, when Dad was
too manic to talk sense to,

17:11.959 --> 17:14.834
he, um, spent all our Christmas money

17:14.917 --> 17:17.917
on stuff he didn't need, but Mom saved up,

17:18.000 --> 17:20.834
and she surprised us with one gift.

17:20.917 --> 17:23.166
A pair of roller skates.

17:23.250 --> 17:24.917
Andrea tried to give them to me,

17:25.000 --> 17:28.375
but I-I put on the left
and he put on the right,

17:28.458 --> 17:33.333
and we held the other
two legs up like flamingos

17:33.417 --> 17:35.875
and skated around the house.

17:37.667 --> 17:39.709
<i>♪ That beauty will find me ♪</i>

17:39.792 --> 17:42.917
Two parts, one whole.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.709
<i>♪ I've seen fire and ashes fall ♪</i>

17:45.792 --> 17:47.333
<i>♪ Will there be someone to save my soul? ♪</i>

17:47.417 --> 17:48.875
Teddy: Looks like the knife went
through the pericardium

17:48.959 --> 17:50.583
and just nicked the ventricle.

17:50.667 --> 17:52.500
You can repair the ventricle
with 3-0 prolene.

17:52.875 --> 17:54.166
Altman?

17:54.250 --> 17:55.417
Yeah, he's right. I'm on it.

17:55.500 --> 17:57.959
-Okay, get in there.
-Right, 3-0 large taper needle.

17:58.041 --> 18:00.041
Damn it. Looks like it's gone through

18:00.125 --> 18:01.875
his spleen, his stomach,
<i>and </i>his diaphragm.

18:01.959 --> 18:03.208
We're gonna have to remove his spleen

18:03.291 --> 18:05.375
and check for intestinal injuries.

18:05.458 --> 18:07.291
Dr. Knox, how many units
has he received so far?

18:07.375 --> 18:09.041
Six units of blood, six of FFP.

18:09.125 --> 18:11.792
Alright, run a TEG to check
for his clotting factors.

18:11.875 --> 18:12.834
[ Sighs ]

18:12.917 --> 18:14.125
You good?

18:14.208 --> 18:15.250
Yep.

18:15.458 --> 18:16.583
Bovie.

18:16.667 --> 18:19.667
<i>♪ Pulls me in and tears me up ♪</i>

18:19.834 --> 18:22.083
Richard: Please don't take this boy.

18:22.166 --> 18:23.500
<i>♪ I hope when I close my eyes ♪</i>

18:23.583 --> 18:25.250
<i>♪ That beauty will find me ♪</i>

18:25.333 --> 18:27.333
Please don't take this boy.

18:29.792 --> 18:32.458
[ Moans, chuckles ]

18:32.542 --> 18:34.375
[ Exhales slowly ]

18:35.291 --> 18:36.333
Mm.

18:39.917 --> 18:41.166
Mm.

18:43.291 --> 18:44.875
[ Both laugh ]

18:44.959 --> 18:45.959
Okay.

18:46.625 --> 18:48.000
Comedy or drama?

18:48.500 --> 18:50.000
[ Both sigh ]

18:50.083 --> 18:51.083
C-SPAN?

18:52.959 --> 18:54.125
[ Laughs ]

18:54.208 --> 18:56.250
Listen, there's something
really soothing about

18:56.333 --> 18:58.625
the whole scrolling at the bottom.

18:58.709 --> 19:00.625
It's like this endless
potential of information.

19:00.709 --> 19:02.125
You're gonna make me read that to you

19:02.208 --> 19:03.542
when we're 80, aren't you?

19:04.375 --> 19:05.959
I mean -- I didn't mean...

19:06.041 --> 19:07.417
Yeah, you did.

19:08.250 --> 19:09.917
You did mean it.

19:11.083 --> 19:12.709
[ Both chuckle ]

19:12.792 --> 19:14.000
Okay.

19:14.083 --> 19:15.625
[ Knock on door ]

19:16.208 --> 19:17.875
Did you order more champagne?

19:17.959 --> 19:19.166
No.

19:19.583 --> 19:21.583
Hold on. I'll get rid of them.

19:22.834 --> 19:24.375
[ Knock on door ]

19:24.458 --> 19:25.834
We're coming.

19:25.917 --> 19:26.875
[ Knocking continues ]

19:26.959 --> 19:28.250
Yeah, we're coming.

19:30.500 --> 19:31.750
[ Knocking continues ]

19:34.125 --> 19:35.417
Hey, uh, can I help you?

19:35.500 --> 19:37.917
Oh, sorry. Wrong -- Wrong room.

19:38.000 --> 19:39.458
Jackson?

19:39.959 --> 19:42.583
Oh, um, this is --
Okay, it's the right room.

19:42.667 --> 19:43.750
Why are you here?

19:43.834 --> 19:45.917
Link called me. You need to come home.

19:52.375 --> 19:53.500
How are we, Knox?

19:53.583 --> 19:54.709
Just hung another two units.

19:54.792 --> 19:56.625
Blood pressure's starting to come up.

19:56.709 --> 19:58.625
-Teddy: Just a few more sutures.
-Nice repair.

19:58.709 --> 19:59.542
I don't see any leak.

19:59.625 --> 20:00.917
Owen: I'm just gonna run
this bowel one more time,

20:01.000 --> 20:02.542
and then I am good to go down here.

20:02.625 --> 20:06.041
Alright, I just need to place the drain,

20:06.125 --> 20:09.041
and then we are good
to start the wire closure.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.000
<i>Great work, everyone.</i>

20:18.917 --> 20:20.125
When was everyone tested?

20:20.208 --> 20:21.333
-Last night.
-Yesterday.

20:21.417 --> 20:22.542
-This morning.
-Alright, come on in.

20:22.625 --> 20:25.500
Amelia's in her room, and, uh,
please keep it down.

20:25.583 --> 20:27.166
This guy just went to sleep.

20:28.709 --> 20:30.000
[ Sighs ]

20:32.041 --> 20:33.125
Anybody want a beer?

20:33.208 --> 20:34.625
-I'm good.
-It's pretty early.

20:34.917 --> 20:35.917
Okay, I'll get some.

20:47.667 --> 20:48.792
[ Sighs ]

20:48.875 --> 20:50.667
The wound was more severe
than we'd hoped,

20:50.750 --> 20:52.041
but he's pulled through.

20:52.125 --> 20:53.291
Oh, my God.

20:53.375 --> 20:54.709
He's alive. Your brother's alive.

20:54.792 --> 20:55.875
Oh, my God!

20:55.959 --> 20:58.375
Oh, it hurts not to hug you right now.

20:58.458 --> 21:00.000
Hey, look at them while you hug me.

21:00.083 --> 21:03.125
[ Laughs ]

21:03.583 --> 21:04.834
Thank you.

21:07.083 --> 21:09.458
Thank you for getting me to help.

21:09.542 --> 21:10.542
Yeah, don't read into it.

21:10.625 --> 21:11.750
I owed it to DeLuca.

21:11.834 --> 21:14.208
And if there was someone else
I could've called, I would've.

21:21.375 --> 21:23.166
Hayes: I said no and I meant it.

21:23.250 --> 21:24.875
I do not take preemies on joyrides.

21:24.959 --> 21:27.208
You're already moving her.
This is just adding a stop.

21:27.291 --> 21:28.917
Plus, I told Val we would make it happen.

21:29.000 --> 21:30.375
Without consulting me first.

21:30.458 --> 21:31.750
It's out of the question.

21:31.959 --> 21:33.500
Get out of my way, Wilson.

21:33.709 --> 21:35.792
Were you nice before your wife died?

21:35.875 --> 21:36.834
Excuse me?

21:36.917 --> 21:38.125
I'm just curious.

21:38.208 --> 21:39.917
You know, I lost the love of my life.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
He didn't die, but he might as well have,

21:42.083 --> 21:44.583
and I was sad and angry and confused,

21:44.667 --> 21:46.250
but I still cared about other people.

21:46.333 --> 21:47.625
In fact, I think it made me care more.

21:47.709 --> 21:49.000
I'm looking out for my patient.

21:49.083 --> 21:50.458
You know this won't jeopardize Luna.

21:50.542 --> 21:51.959
Grey was laughing and joking,

21:52.041 --> 21:53.709
and a few hours later she's on a vent.

21:53.792 --> 21:55.917
This is not the time to play
fast and loose with rules

21:56.000 --> 21:57.333
that keep our patients safe.

21:57.417 --> 21:59.500
If it was Meredith Grey
asking to see her child,

21:59.583 --> 22:00.625
would you say the same thing?

22:04.250 --> 22:06.208
Five minutes, not a second longer.

22:14.500 --> 22:15.834
Ah. Ah.

22:18.208 --> 22:21.500
ABG's the same as this morning,

22:22.000 --> 22:24.250
but no fever and labs are decent.

22:25.125 --> 22:26.333
DeLuca's awake.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.834
-Does Bailey know?
-She's still sleeping,

22:28.917 --> 22:30.917
but, uh, I'll tell her in a bit.

22:31.458 --> 22:33.000
That was a great save, Altman.

22:33.542 --> 22:34.667
Thank you.

22:35.458 --> 22:37.750
I'm gonna go check on my other patients.

22:39.041 --> 22:42.250
<i>♪ I've been here all day ♪</i>

22:43.041 --> 22:45.083
<i>♪ It's too hot to sleep ♪</i>

22:46.500 --> 22:48.375
<i>♪ Time is running away ♪</i>

22:48.458 --> 22:50.125
I don't regret it.

22:50.208 --> 22:51.417
How did you know I was wondering that?

22:51.667 --> 22:52.917
I don't know.

22:53.000 --> 22:54.375
I just did.

22:55.500 --> 22:56.583
I don't regret it.

22:57.166 --> 22:58.583
You know, we walk through our lives

22:58.667 --> 22:59.792
and we witness atrocities.

22:59.875 --> 23:01.917
See homeless people
on the street asking for help

23:02.000 --> 23:03.583
and we just walk right past them.

23:04.375 --> 23:06.875
See people that can't pay
for medicine for their children,

23:06.959 --> 23:08.250
see people beating their kids,

23:08.333 --> 23:09.834
and we just say, "Well,
it's none of our business."

23:10.000 --> 23:11.792
See atrocities on the news every day.

23:12.583 --> 23:14.625
Crimes and cruelties committed
by our government,

23:14.709 --> 23:17.375
paid for, nonetheless,
by our own tax dollars.

23:19.250 --> 23:21.166
And what do we do? We just
change the channel, right?

23:21.250 --> 23:23.417
We just -- We tune it out.

23:23.625 --> 23:26.041
Then we go back to work and we
pretend like what we just saw,

23:26.125 --> 23:30.083
or that article we just read was
somehow normal or acceptable,

23:30.166 --> 23:31.667
and the people who take to the streets

23:31.750 --> 23:33.250
screaming out for change,

23:33.875 --> 23:35.375
they're written off as crazy,

23:35.458 --> 23:37.041
they're written off as extreme.

23:37.291 --> 23:38.542
Doesn't make any sense.

23:39.333 --> 23:40.583
Makes no sense.

23:41.000 --> 23:42.542
But what you did, Meredith,

23:42.625 --> 23:44.583
risking your medical license
to save that little girl--

23:44.667 --> 23:45.959
that made sense.

23:46.041 --> 23:47.458
And what I did-- following that woman,

23:47.542 --> 23:49.000
not letting up, not letting her get away,

23:49.083 --> 23:51.625
not letting her harm
another single human being.

23:52.041 --> 23:54.208
Yeah, it was dangerous, but it made sense.

23:55.500 --> 23:57.041
It's the only thing that made sense.

23:59.250 --> 24:01.000
So I don't regret it.

24:03.125 --> 24:06.000
<i>♪ But I'm standing still ♪</i>

24:06.208 --> 24:07.667
Owen: He suffered a lot of bleeding,

24:07.750 --> 24:09.083
but his vitals are stable.

24:09.166 --> 24:10.417
Oh, Andrea.

24:10.500 --> 24:13.083
<i>♪ Is so vacant and numb ♪</i>

24:13.166 --> 24:14.667
Hey, hey.

24:14.750 --> 24:16.417
<i>♪ I can't even remember what it was ♪</i>

24:16.500 --> 24:17.959
Hey.

24:18.041 --> 24:20.458
Easy, easy, don't try to talk.

24:21.667 --> 24:23.250
You did it. It's over.

24:23.333 --> 24:24.500
They arrested the woman,

24:24.583 --> 24:26.000
they arrested the man who stabbed you.

24:26.083 --> 24:28.083
You saved so many children, Andrea.

24:28.291 --> 24:31.417
[ Speaking Italian ]

24:32.542 --> 24:34.625
[ in English ] Now,
blink once for morphine

24:34.709 --> 24:37.125
and twice for "I'm a dummy
who will never ignore

24:37.208 --> 24:38.792
his sister ever again."

24:38.875 --> 24:40.291
<i>♪ Is more than I can bear ♪</i>

24:40.375 --> 24:41.542
[ Chuckles ]

24:41.625 --> 24:44.166
[ Speaks Italian ]

24:44.250 --> 24:46.583
<i>♪ It's not dark yet ♪</i>

24:47.875 --> 24:49.875
<i>♪ But it's getting there ♪</i>

24:55.625 --> 24:56.875
[ Cellphone keyboard clacking ]

24:59.166 --> 25:02.166
[ in English ] What was the surgery?
I want details.

25:04.625 --> 25:07.583
It was a trauma. It went well.

25:07.667 --> 25:10.417
Your oxygen saturation's gone up.

25:10.834 --> 25:12.417
That's encouraging.

25:19.917 --> 25:21.166
I did love you,

25:21.250 --> 25:23.125
even though I tried so hard
not to love you

25:23.208 --> 25:24.959
because I also loved Owen.

25:25.041 --> 25:26.834
I think I thought
that I could love you both,

25:26.917 --> 25:29.000
but instead, I just--
I tore it all to the ground

25:29.083 --> 25:30.959
and took you both with me.

25:31.500 --> 25:33.542
[ Chuckling ] Wow.

25:34.792 --> 25:37.291
I asked you for one thing, Altman.

25:37.458 --> 25:39.375
You asked me for the truth.

25:39.458 --> 25:40.959
No, no. I didn't ask you for that

25:41.041 --> 25:42.792
because the truth is relative.

25:42.875 --> 25:45.041
You got yourself convinced
that you loved us both,

25:45.125 --> 25:47.458
but empirical evidence
would suggest otherwise.

25:47.542 --> 25:48.583
Empirical? I--

25:48.667 --> 25:49.792
He doesn't want you.

25:54.041 --> 25:55.458
You're right, you dragged us
both to the ground,

25:55.542 --> 25:56.834
but he doesn't want anything
to do with you

25:56.917 --> 25:58.291
and I'm still here sitting in the dust.

25:58.375 --> 26:01.750
If you loved me, Teddy, we'd be together

26:01.834 --> 26:05.667
instead of... together in our misery.

26:07.041 --> 26:08.709
Empirical evidence.

26:10.750 --> 26:14.125
I asked you to admit you never
loved me because...

26:17.125 --> 26:18.166
I need it.

26:19.834 --> 26:23.542
If I survive this thing...

26:26.542 --> 26:29.500
...I want to get up off the ground
where you dropped me, so...

26:32.417 --> 26:33.542
...I need it.

26:45.083 --> 26:46.709
I never loved you, Tom.

26:48.333 --> 26:49.667
[ Scoffs ]

26:53.083 --> 26:54.500
Thank you.

26:59.333 --> 27:00.500
Jackson: You want to sit, or...

27:00.583 --> 27:02.417
Oh, the second I stop,

27:02.500 --> 27:04.083
Scout starts wailing
like a human ambulance.

27:04.166 --> 27:05.417
As you were.

27:05.500 --> 27:07.208
And Scout needs me to keep moving.

27:07.291 --> 27:11.333
Zola, Bailey, Ellis--
they need us to keep on moving,

27:11.417 --> 27:12.875
playing songs and eating.

27:12.959 --> 27:14.291
They eat so much.

27:14.375 --> 27:16.083
So I just keep going to the grocery store

27:16.166 --> 27:18.375
and buying food
that Amelia keeps pretending

27:18.458 --> 27:19.917
she knows how to cook,

27:20.250 --> 27:22.041
and what if Meredith doesn't survive this,

27:22.125 --> 27:23.709
you know what it's gonna do to my life?

27:24.917 --> 27:26.959
Yeah, you just said that out loud.

27:27.041 --> 27:28.041
Don't worry about it, we're all scared.

27:28.125 --> 27:29.417
No one's judging you.

27:29.500 --> 27:30.667
Winston: I'm a little bit judging,

27:30.750 --> 27:32.792
but that's 'cause I've only
known you seven minutes.

27:33.792 --> 27:36.625
I'm on my knees every night
praying that she survives this,

27:36.709 --> 27:38.834
and I'm not an
on-my-knees-praying kind of guy.

27:38.917 --> 27:40.625
-I get it.
-I'm not praying for myself.

27:40.709 --> 27:42.458
You're human, Link.
Give yourself a break, alright?

27:42.542 --> 27:44.125
You're exhausted.

27:44.208 --> 27:46.542
Meredith is-- she's family to me.

27:46.625 --> 27:48.875
I mean, Meredith is family.

27:49.125 --> 27:53.125
I can think of a million reasons
I don't want her to... die.

27:53.208 --> 27:55.041
Some of them are about her,
some are about me,

27:55.125 --> 27:56.500
some are about the world at large.

27:56.583 --> 27:58.375
Point is, you're allowed
to have your reasons.

27:58.458 --> 28:00.083
They don't all have to be selfless.

28:00.166 --> 28:01.166
I just...

28:02.959 --> 28:04.917
I mean, those kids already lost their dad.

28:05.333 --> 28:07.875
I don't want them to have
to grow up without a mom, too.

28:09.875 --> 28:11.041
And all we can do is just --

28:11.125 --> 28:12.250
Keep moving.

28:12.333 --> 28:13.375
Yeah.

28:13.458 --> 28:14.959
I mean, literally keep moving,

28:15.041 --> 28:16.417
'cause human ambulance.

28:16.500 --> 28:18.000
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

28:18.083 --> 28:19.542
You know, you're pretty good at this.

28:19.625 --> 28:21.208
The whole "keep somebody calm

28:21.291 --> 28:23.291
you've only known seven minutes" thing.

28:24.166 --> 28:27.041
Well, to be fair, it's been more
like eight minutes now.

28:27.125 --> 28:28.125
It's true.

28:28.375 --> 28:30.709
And, Jackson, thank you
for getting Maggie over here.

28:30.792 --> 28:32.333
I-I-I'm sorry if that was awkward.

28:32.417 --> 28:34.166
-You were the only one picking up.
-No, it's fine.

28:34.250 --> 28:35.917
Why would it be awkward?

28:39.417 --> 28:40.875
Uh, just...

28:42.000 --> 28:43.125
Yeah.

28:43.583 --> 28:46.792
Okay, you're, uh --
you're her ex, aren't you?

28:46.875 --> 28:48.500
Mm. Another round?

28:48.583 --> 28:49.709
Yeah.

28:49.792 --> 28:51.000
[ Sighs ]

28:54.709 --> 28:58.583
I was Zola and Bailey and Ellis.

28:58.667 --> 29:00.709
I was the kid who lost a parent

29:00.792 --> 29:02.166
and the world turned upside down.

29:03.750 --> 29:05.208
And I don't know...

29:06.250 --> 29:09.208
if I hadn't been there to see
my dad dead on the ground,

29:09.291 --> 29:11.500
how long they would've waited to tell me.

29:15.166 --> 29:16.500
Nobody talked about it.

29:18.333 --> 29:20.583
I didn't expect answers, but...

29:22.750 --> 29:24.583
there wasn't room for questions.

29:25.583 --> 29:29.125
Just... silence.

29:29.917 --> 29:32.000
Meredith told the kids about Derek.

29:34.083 --> 29:35.500
We can do this for her.

29:35.583 --> 29:36.875
She deserves us

29:37.792 --> 29:39.208
stepping up.

29:40.417 --> 29:41.917
And the kids do, too.

29:43.458 --> 29:45.625
Can we just stay here a little longer?

29:55.083 --> 29:57.542
Your mom is gonna freak out
when she sees you.

29:57.625 --> 29:58.959
Yes, she is.

29:59.041 --> 30:01.166
Woman on PA: <i>Code blue, code blue.</i>

30:01.458 --> 30:02.583
<i>Code blue.</i>

30:02.667 --> 30:04.083
Val's coding! Hurry!

30:04.166 --> 30:05.250
No.

30:05.333 --> 30:06.667
No, no, no.

30:09.625 --> 30:10.959
Hey.

30:11.750 --> 30:13.000
Comfortable?

30:13.750 --> 30:15.250
Well, your sister just went to get coffee,

30:15.333 --> 30:16.834
but she left strict instructions.

30:17.667 --> 30:19.000
No car chases, okay?

30:19.250 --> 30:20.834
[ Chuckles ]

30:24.583 --> 30:26.083
[ Clears throat ] Okay.

30:26.542 --> 30:28.083
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

30:28.208 --> 30:30.000
He's tachycardic and his CVP's going up.

30:31.083 --> 30:32.500
Woman on PA: <i>Code blue, code blue.</i>

30:32.583 --> 30:33.875
Must be cardiac tamponade.

30:33.959 --> 30:35.542
We're gonna have
to open him back up again.

30:35.625 --> 30:37.166
Let's get a scalpel and order more blood.

30:37.250 --> 30:39.500
Woman on PA: <i>Code blue, code blue.</i>

30:39.583 --> 30:42.083
DeLuca? DeLuca, we're gonna have
to open you back up, okay?

30:42.166 --> 30:43.834
But I am with you, okay?

30:43.917 --> 30:45.125
I got you, okay?

30:45.208 --> 30:46.750
Come on. Staple remover.

30:46.834 --> 30:48.041
Thank you.

30:48.166 --> 30:49.834
[ Monitor continues to beep rapidly ]

30:49.917 --> 30:52.083
Come on, come on, come on, come on.

30:52.166 --> 30:53.875
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

30:53.959 --> 30:54.959
Okay, wire cutters.

30:56.709 --> 30:57.959
Okay.

31:00.291 --> 31:01.583
Good, let's go.

31:01.667 --> 31:03.208
One, two, three.

31:03.333 --> 31:04.583
[ Grunts ]

31:07.625 --> 31:10.500
Somebody page Altman and have
her meet me in the OR!

31:19.959 --> 31:21.583
Owen: [ Muffled ] Call for more blood.

31:21.667 --> 31:23.583
Start the massive transfusion protocol.

31:23.667 --> 31:25.125
<i>♪ Black water fills the room</i>
<i>all around me ♪</i>

31:25.208 --> 31:26.291
Almost there, DeLuca, okay?

31:26.375 --> 31:27.834
Let's go, let's go!

31:27.917 --> 31:29.166
Jo: Charge to 150. Clear.

31:29.458 --> 31:30.834
[ Paddles whine ]

31:31.125 --> 31:32.291
-[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]
-Come on, Val!

31:32.375 --> 31:33.583
You're so close to seeing your baby girl.

31:34.625 --> 31:35.792
Charged to 200.

31:36.208 --> 31:37.500
Clear.

31:37.583 --> 31:38.542
[ Paddles whine ]

31:39.834 --> 31:42.041
<i>♪ My fingers turning red ♪</i>

31:42.250 --> 31:43.375
What happened?

31:43.458 --> 31:45.041
He went into DIC. He's bleeding out.

31:45.125 --> 31:47.250
-Push TXA --
-Dr. Knox: I already have.

31:47.333 --> 31:48.500
Push more.

31:48.583 --> 31:49.583
Teddy: I'm gonna need
a ton of lap pads.

31:49.667 --> 31:50.709
Let me in.

31:51.917 --> 31:55.583
<i>♪ I can feel it slowly caving in ♪</i>

31:56.291 --> 31:58.291
<i>♪ I can feel it ♪</i>

32:00.709 --> 32:02.917
<i>♪ I can feel it ♪</i>

32:03.000 --> 32:04.083
[ Monitor beeping ]

32:04.166 --> 32:05.166
He's crashing.

32:05.250 --> 32:06.583
Starting cardiac massage.

32:09.166 --> 32:11.834
<i>♪ I can feel it ♪</i>

32:11.917 --> 32:13.500
Charge to 270.

32:13.625 --> 32:14.875
I think it's too late.

32:15.250 --> 32:16.542
Clear.

32:16.917 --> 32:18.542
[ Paddles whine ]

32:20.375 --> 32:21.917
[ Sighs ]

32:22.000 --> 32:24.792
<i>♪ I can barely feel my heart beat ♪</i>

32:24.875 --> 32:27.625
So, this morning they put
your mom on a ventilator.

32:28.542 --> 32:30.709
That's the machine that breathes for her.

32:31.125 --> 32:32.333
Yeah.

32:32.458 --> 32:33.917
When will they take her off of it?

32:34.083 --> 32:36.417
Different people come off of it
at different times.

32:39.000 --> 32:40.500
My dad never did.

32:41.417 --> 32:42.875
Do you think my mom will?

32:46.375 --> 32:47.875
We hope so.

32:47.959 --> 32:49.667
But we don't know.

32:49.750 --> 32:51.625
We just --

32:51.709 --> 32:53.000
We don't know.

32:57.041 --> 32:59.208
We shouldn't tell Bailey and Ellis.

33:00.667 --> 33:02.375
Not unless we need to.

33:03.125 --> 33:05.125
They're just too young to understand.

33:05.333 --> 33:07.458
Okay. We'll wait.

33:17.625 --> 33:20.750
[ Slow music playing ]

33:27.667 --> 33:29.000
[ Door opens ]

33:40.583 --> 33:41.959
Hayes: No respiratory distress,

33:42.041 --> 33:44.000
chest tube's barely putting out anything.

33:44.083 --> 33:45.125
Thank you.

33:45.375 --> 33:46.625
She's a trouper.

33:46.709 --> 33:47.834
She's gonna need to be.

33:49.250 --> 33:50.417
No.

33:50.917 --> 33:53.000
I ran the code for an hour.

34:00.166 --> 34:01.250
You know...

34:01.333 --> 34:02.291
[ Clears throat ]

34:02.375 --> 34:03.625
I was nicer...

34:05.917 --> 34:07.208
before Abigail died.

34:07.709 --> 34:10.125
I was a great deal many things,
most of them better.

34:11.375 --> 34:12.625
I'm sorry, I never should've--

34:12.709 --> 34:15.417
Oh, it was kind
what you wanted to do, it was.

34:15.959 --> 34:17.083
I'm so sorry.

34:17.583 --> 34:19.000
Me too.

34:34.041 --> 34:36.500
[ Music playing ]

34:42.750 --> 34:44.458
[ Door opens ]

35:01.041 --> 35:02.291
[ Door opens ]

35:06.291 --> 35:07.375
[ Door closes ]

35:08.208 --> 35:09.583
Val is dead.

35:09.667 --> 35:10.875
I heard.

35:12.917 --> 35:14.083
I'm sorry.

35:14.959 --> 35:17.417
DeLuca was okay and now he might not be.

35:24.375 --> 35:27.000
I spent so many years
pretending to be someone else.

35:29.083 --> 35:31.458
So many years afraid
of what my mother thought,

35:31.542 --> 35:33.458
neighbors thought, what I thought.

35:37.041 --> 35:38.709
I wasted so much time.

35:40.041 --> 35:44.792
And now we're all just working
and surviving and waiting.

35:44.875 --> 35:46.125
[ Chuckles ]

35:46.625 --> 35:47.792
For what?

35:50.583 --> 35:52.250
Is this all just gonna end one day?

35:52.333 --> 35:55.125
Like, one day we're all gonna get a memo

35:55.208 --> 35:58.125
that says, "COVID's over.
Everyone back to normal"?

35:59.750 --> 36:02.542
I think I wasted all the time
I was supposed to be happy.

36:05.875 --> 36:07.583
[ Crying ]

36:17.542 --> 36:18.875
Bailey: Mm.

36:21.291 --> 36:23.166
How long have I been asleep?

36:23.250 --> 36:25.250
Richard: Uh, most of the day.

36:25.333 --> 36:27.208
[ Grunts ]

36:27.291 --> 36:29.959
Bailey, something's happened.

36:30.834 --> 36:32.625
No, it's -- it's not Meredith.

36:33.750 --> 36:34.709
It's DeLuca.

36:34.792 --> 36:36.083
What?

36:38.125 --> 36:39.542
Richard, what?

36:41.417 --> 36:42.917
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

36:47.458 --> 36:48.834
Okay, give me 1 of epi.

36:53.875 --> 36:55.792
[ Teddy speaking indistinctly ]

36:59.333 --> 37:00.709
Meredith: The tide is coming in!

37:00.792 --> 37:02.166
I know.

37:02.250 --> 37:03.667
It's gonna wash it away.

37:03.750 --> 37:05.375
I know, I'm trying to beat it.

37:06.250 --> 37:07.250
You're trying to beat the tide?

37:07.333 --> 37:08.291
Yeah.

37:08.375 --> 37:09.375
I had more to do.

37:09.458 --> 37:10.625
I had plans.

37:10.959 --> 37:12.667
Wanted to do another tower over here

37:12.750 --> 37:15.333
and a-- a-- a bridge with a moat.

37:16.333 --> 37:18.083
Tide's coming in too fast.

37:19.291 --> 37:21.083
Come on. It's too fast.

37:21.166 --> 37:22.542
I had plans.

37:25.083 --> 37:26.542
[ Groans ] Come on.

37:26.625 --> 37:28.458
You can't build a sand castle
without a moat.

37:30.625 --> 37:32.625
I don't know what happens
from here, Meredith.

37:33.542 --> 37:34.709
Meredith: Me either.

37:36.750 --> 37:38.500
DeLuca: But no matter what happens,

37:38.583 --> 37:41.709
I want you to know that I never
felt seen the way you saw me.

37:41.792 --> 37:44.500
I never felt inspired
the way you inspired me.

37:44.583 --> 37:46.500
You made me want to be
not just my best self,

37:46.583 --> 37:48.125
but better.

37:48.208 --> 37:50.333
And yeah, I felt small
around you sometimes.

37:50.417 --> 37:51.792
I felt insecure.

37:52.166 --> 37:55.417
I wanted something from you that
I needed to give to myself.

37:56.166 --> 37:58.667
But here, now, on this beach with you,

37:58.750 --> 38:01.417
I...I get it.

38:02.333 --> 38:03.834
I don't just get it, I <i>feel </i>it.

38:04.250 --> 38:05.583
I get who I am.

38:05.667 --> 38:07.750
I know my own soul, my strength.

38:10.417 --> 38:12.166
Do you want to take a walk?

38:12.458 --> 38:14.625
We can watch the sunset from the dock.

38:15.208 --> 38:16.750
In a minute.

38:17.834 --> 38:19.917
I just want to feel this first.

38:21.333 --> 38:23.375
I just want to hold onto this
a little longer.

38:23.458 --> 38:25.208
Meredith: <i>I'm a little bit of an exception</i>

38:25.291 --> 38:27.291
<i>when it comes to having a happy place.</i>

38:27.834 --> 38:30.083
<i>Because the hospital's always been mine.</i>

38:30.166 --> 38:31.417
Internal paddles.

38:31.500 --> 38:33.166
-Come on, come on.
-Owen: Let's go, let's go.

38:33.250 --> 38:35.250
<i>♪ And there could be a place ♪</i>

38:35.333 --> 38:36.458
Charge to 20.

38:36.542 --> 38:37.500
[ Paddles whine ]

38:37.583 --> 38:39.166
Clear.

38:40.667 --> 38:41.625
Again.

38:41.709 --> 38:42.875
Clear.

38:42.959 --> 38:44.250
[ Paddles whine ]

38:44.333 --> 38:45.417
Charge to 30.

38:45.542 --> 38:46.500
-Clear.
-[ Paddles whine ]

38:46.583 --> 38:47.667
Come on.

38:47.750 --> 38:48.792
-Again.
-Again.

38:48.875 --> 38:49.834
Clear.

38:49.917 --> 38:51.917
[ Paddles whine ]

38:52.000 --> 38:54.041
<i>♪ Always so far ♪</i>

38:54.125 --> 38:55.667
Teddy: Come on.

38:55.750 --> 38:57.959
<i>♪ Always so near ♪</i>

38:58.041 --> 38:59.709
Meredith: <i>Maybe it's because</i>
<i>it's where I grew up.</i>

38:59.792 --> 39:03.125
<i>♪ Who cast the spell ♪</i>

39:03.208 --> 39:05.834
<i>♪ Of our fair weather ♪</i>

39:05.917 --> 39:07.208
Woman: Andrea!

39:07.291 --> 39:10.834
<i>♪ The sweet hellos ♪</i>

39:11.208 --> 39:14.250
<i>♪ The fair farewells ♪</i>

39:15.959 --> 39:17.500
Mom?

39:17.583 --> 39:18.709
[ Chuckling ] Mom?

39:18.792 --> 39:20.500
Andrea!

39:24.208 --> 39:25.792
Meredith: I'll miss you.

39:27.500 --> 39:29.250
If I go back and you don't,

39:30.333 --> 39:31.625
I'll miss you.

39:33.375 --> 39:34.834
It'll be okay, Meredith.

39:36.125 --> 39:37.750
It will. It'll be okay.

39:38.959 --> 39:40.333
Woman: Andrea!

39:40.959 --> 39:42.333
I have to go.

39:42.417 --> 39:43.750
Okay.

39:50.959 --> 39:53.041
[ Speaks Italian ]

39:53.333 --> 39:54.834
Mama!

39:54.917 --> 39:56.750
<i>♪ Where the wind may blow ♪</i>

39:57.000 --> 39:58.959
[ Speaks Italian ]

39:59.041 --> 40:01.458
<i>♪ I've never been a man ♪</i>

40:01.542 --> 40:02.959
<i>♪ For another's shadows ♪</i>

40:03.041 --> 40:04.667
-Oh!
-[ Chuckles ]

40:05.375 --> 40:08.375
<i>♪ But sometimes I ♪</i>

40:08.458 --> 40:12.000
<i>♪ Drive by the place you live ♪</i>

40:12.083 --> 40:15.875
<i>-♪ Just hoping I ♪</i>
-[ Laughter ]

40:15.959 --> 40:17.166
<i>♪ Might catch you in the windows ♪</i>

40:17.250 --> 40:19.750
[ Suction gurgling ]

40:19.834 --> 40:22.500
<i>♪ Well, if you've known love ♪</i>

40:23.291 --> 40:25.208
Reza: His heart won't restart.

40:25.625 --> 40:28.250
He's been down for 40 minutes.

40:28.333 --> 40:32.125
<i>♪ The sun and then the bloody rain ♪</i>

40:36.333 --> 40:38.792
<i>♪ And though there's nothing ♪</i>

40:39.709 --> 40:41.834
<i>♪ Nothing to forgive ♪</i>

40:43.041 --> 40:46.750
<i>♪ If we could find the grace ♪</i>

40:46.834 --> 40:50.500
<i>♪ There could be a place ♪</i>

40:50.625 --> 40:52.792
<i>♪ There could be a place ♪</i>

40:52.875 --> 40:55.041
[ Flatline ]

40:58.625 --> 41:00.458
Isn't somebody going to call it?

41:00.542 --> 41:02.583
[ Flatlining continues ]

41:10.250 --> 41:11.917
[ Tools clang ]

41:25.208 --> 41:28.542
Time of death -- 22:50.

41:34.542 --> 41:39.542
<i>♪ Ohh ♪</i>

41:39.625 --> 41:44.125
<i>♪ Ohh ♪</i>

41:44.208 --> 41:46.750
<i>♪ Another life ♪</i>

41:46.834 --> 41:48.166
Meredith: <i>But if you're not like me...</i>

41:48.250 --> 41:50.583
<i>♪ Another time ♪</i>

41:51.583 --> 41:54.375
<i>♪ Could there be a place ♪</i>

41:55.417 --> 41:57.250
<i>♪ For you and I? ♪</i>

41:59.166 --> 42:01.291
<i>♪ Abandon reason ♪</i>

42:02.834 --> 42:04.959
<i>♪ Adopt the rhyme ♪</i>

42:05.834 --> 42:07.959
<i>♪ And there could be a place ♪</i>

42:08.041 --> 42:09.959
<i>...you're going to want somewhere else.</i>

42:10.041 --> 42:12.250
<i>♪ For us to find ♪</i>

42:13.500 --> 42:16.542
<i>♪ There could be a place ♪</i>

42:22.625 --> 42:24.458
[ Closing theme music playing ]
